-- Noble Energy to replace Archstone-Smith in S&P 500
-- 
-- Mon Oct 1, 2007 7:17pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/01/us-standardpoors-indices-idUSWEN141820071001

 

 LOS ANGELES  (Reuters) - Standard & Poor's said on Monday that S&P MidCap 400 Index constituent Noble Energy Inc ( NBL.N ) will replace Archstone-Smith Trust ( ASN.N ) on the large-cap S&P 500 Index after the close of trading on Friday. 

 Apartment landlord Archstone is being acquired by U.S. brokerage Lehman Brothers Holdings Inc LEH.N and property developer Tishman Speyer in a deal valued at about $22 billion including assumed debt. Lamar Advertising Co ( LAMR.O ) will replace Noble Energy in the S&P MidCap 400 and Ashford Hospitality Trust Inc ( AHT.N ) will replace Archstone-Smith in the S&P REIT Composite. (Reporting by  Lisa Baertlein )